TITLE: Using Authentication Store in React Native Component
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use the authentication store in a React Native component. It shows importing the store, hydrating it on app start, and using its state and actions within a component.
SOURCE: https://github.com/obytes/react-native-template-obytes/blob/master/docs/src/content/docs/guides/authentication.mdx#2025-04-18_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: TSX
CODE:
```
import { useAuth, hydrate } from '@/lib';

hydrate(); // call this when the application is started to check if the user is authenticated or not

const App = () => {
  const status = useAuth.use.status();
  const signOut = useAuth.use.signOut();

  return (
    <View>
      <Text>{status}</Text>
      <Button title="Sign Out" onPress={signOut} />
    </View>
